  "timeboxMinutes": 15,
  "prompt": "You need every employee in the `engineering` department.\n\nWrite `fetch_engineers(base_url, token)`. Call `GET {base_url}/v1/employees`, pass a bearer auth header, ask the server for `department=engineering`, follow every cursor, and return the matching employee dictionaries.\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return `list[dict]`.\n- Each dict should be one employee object from the API, unchanged.\n- Return only employees whose `department` is exactly `\"engineering\"`.\n- Preserve the API order after filtering.\n- If no engineers exist, return `[]`.\n\nEmployee shape:\n\n```python\n{\"id\": \"emp_001\", \"name\": \"Ada Lovelace\", \"email\": \"emp_001@ramp.test\", \"department\": \"engineering\"}\n```\n\nEndpoint details:\n\n- `GET {base_url}/v1/employees` requires `headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {token}\"}`.\n- It supports `params={\"department\": \"engineering\", \"limit\": 5, \"cursor\": cursor}`.\n- Responses are paginated as `{\"data\": [...], \"next_cursor\": \"...\" | None}`.\n\nThe test harness passes `token` into your function. Do not define or hardcode it; use the `token` parameter when building the `Authorization` header.\n\nInvariants and corner cases:\n\n- Use the server-side `department` filter; the tests reject fetching all employees for this problem.\n- Start with no cursor, then pass back `next_cursor` until it is `None`.\n- Do not hardcode the token string. Hidden tests use a different token.\n- Do not return finance/product/sales employees.\n\nShared fake API note: this uses the in-process `requests` mock described in the Ramp Travel module guide; there is no real network.\n\nValidation focus: auth header, server-side filter, pagination, order, no duplicates, and custom-token hidden cases.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "fetchEngineers",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
